Mother's school is also part of the offices that have included architects.
the administrative building Avriopoint in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected that it also houses a mini motherhood school with all the necessary - colour walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, the children of the employees of Arch. design can go there.
The architectonic project company Arch. Design. whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has imagined its mini-maternal school of business since the first drafts of the building Avriopoint.
It employs about 90 people, especially from the age of children, and it was important for women architects and project leaders to be able to return to work quickly.
At the same time as low-time employment contracts, the maternal school is a bonus offered to its employees by Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Manufacturers and architects thus have the opportunity to combine work with care for children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who imagined this mother's school and with the support of management that they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-maternal school is funded through the European Social Fund through the operational programme of human resources and the State budget of the Czech Republic.
With funding facilities (up to 2.8 thousand Czech crowns) they were able to purchase equipment and equipment and after two years provide qualified personnel and start-up.
After the use of the funding allocation (two years) Arch. Design. company has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini-maternal school on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted for one year and it was the company Economy rating that helped to apply for staffing.
Child care is provided by qualified staff, all day a nurse and mother's teacher take care of children. Children can go to mother's school without age limitation but they are more than three years old for most.
As it is a "mini maternal school" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more to replace.
The functioning of the school is flexible according to the needs of parents and children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is an individual care and education, the mini-maternal school program is comparable to that for preschool education.
Children do not just play it, but quality education is also provided - from the beginning to the preparation of schools, English is taught.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can control their children at any time and not have the stress of a delay to go to a remote school from the parent's workplace.
Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty between the employee and the employer is created.
Arch.Design.s is thus registered among companies that offer a bonus of choice for recruiting new employees and are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens HR marketing.
The house still fascinates after 100 years. Look into Gaudi's interiors.
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric sarian, the staircase with a dinosaur spine and the balconies with open fish mouths.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic forms, the house received the nickname of House in bone from the premises.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, pieces of tiles and mosaics, façade recalling scales and everywhere present of curves, here is all that is ypic for Art Nouveau d'Antoni Gaudi.
The front of the house runs its dream lines, its pleasant colours and textures that remind nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation, you can see geometry, rhythm and order that are precisely thought.
In the night the façade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of the colors is reinforced.
Rolling and twisting of shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
Wood copies window frames, balustrades, decorative elements of the doors, the eyepiece and the blades.
The Battlo house that stands in the Eixample district on the March Street Passeig de Gracia at number. 43, was born of the construction of a house of 1877 by architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took place for two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of old construction and the construction of another all new but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of unusual reconstruction and better market.
But Casa Battlo's idea as a house with multiple homes was not thought by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol was working with him.
It is precisely on his project that decorations were born for an apartment representation of the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade.
Other artists and creators have also worked for the facade.
The joint work for the plans of Casa Battlo began with successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of the house of Gaudi Casa Mila and Guell Park in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The premises nicknamed the house hot just after it was finished due to its organic forms "the House in Bone".
Others, in view of the specific opening mechanism of the windows called it "the house that dances".
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of Saint Georges the patron of Catalonia.
Other elements of sculpture of the construction contain hidden religious motives.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time, with air events and typical fireplaces.
Their 45-degree inclination seems strange.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely failed to comply with the construction directives and did not allow themselves to be hampered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained permission from the city to build, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the completion the municipal council was horrified and demanded changes.
He did not, for example, like members of the municipal council that construction pillars were impeding on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call from Josep Battlo demanded (and got satisfaction) the permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common lounge and on the third there was a room and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase through which you can access up to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and replaced by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of space linkage.
The common part can be fully connected by opening the doors of the salons and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi received in addition to new facades a non-traditional roof and two floors in addition.
Gaudi's game with light is also impressive, blue and white glass tiles with which is decorated the inner courtyard and with light wells.
The two-color game gives maximum light on all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that white reflects more than the dark that instead absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house which was registered in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund may be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued their visits because they found it to be a lucrative company and they expanded the field of visits to common spaces and barns, including roof terraces.
The ticket to the monument is not really expensive and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and holders of tourist maps have 20 percent discount.
The amount is still above the entry price in other Gaudi buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic towers, you must quickly find a friend among the residents of the building and visit the house completely.
