The seniors experienced a slight rise in unemployment, at 6.4% in metropolis (+0.2 points per three months and one year), 482,000 people aged 50 years or older, and 6.6% with the DOM.
Only 25-49 years have benefited from unemployment stability in the third quarter, at 8.3% in metropolis (-0.1 point over three months, +0.1 point over one year) and 8.8% throughout France.
